metadata.name: Echoes #28
metadata.description:
"The stars were also temporal travelers. How many of these ancestral flashes of light were echoes of long-gone suns? And how many awaited their birth, whose brightness had not yet reached us? If all the suns were to fade away, except for ours, how long would it take for us to realize our solitude? I always knew that the firmament harbored mysteries, but only now do I understand that the earth is also shrouded in enigmas."

Project created in p5.js
Press "s" to save the image.

metadata.name: 8x8 Pixel Creatures #126
metadata.description:
Pixel art is a highly relevant art form, which rarely gets the kudos it deserves from the wider art world. 

I wanted to include some small pixel art creations in another project I was working on. However, I got a bit carried away, and ended up creating a pixel creature generator.

I came to like these little pixel creatures, so I decided to share them, and give them a life on FxHash - I hope you like them too. 

There are a bunch of variations, and a reasonable chance one or two styles may never be minted, so mint away, and I hope you get a rare one. Also, minters get a share in future royalties of their mints, which may be cool in any reality where they become popular one day.

I'll probably reference these guys on other relevant art I produce, when it seems appropriate.

Coded in p5js.

metadata.name: Last Lines #98
metadata.description:
How many lines have been drawn on fxhash since that first generative logo started growing on a Wednesday in early November? How many brush strokes, wires, cables, threads? Many thousands per mint? Millions per project? Billions in total? Shall we add just a few more to celebrate the end of the genesis? Here are 222 iterations with 111 lines each. Each line connects two edges of the canvas but may get deflected by hidden attractors in an attempt to minimize friction and deviation from its path.

Press [p]rint to save a high resolution capture.

This artwork is fully generative and was entirely hand-coded in 4,400 characters of plain JavaScript. Forever limited to 222 editions on the Tezos blockchain. I hope you will enjoy yours. London, March 2022.

metadata.name: SQUARE GAMES #200
metadata.description:
Quite frankely: a lot of squares

An exploration of recursion
featuring very vibrant color combinations
Interactive

4 recursion depths
16 color palettes
4 expansion states
4 fill probabilities 
4 ghost probabilities 

Press 's' to save a high res image
Click and move mouse to explore
Press 'space' to return to original position
Press 'b' to change color of white cube
Press ‚f‘ for fullscreen
Press 'p‘ to toggle pixel perfect rendering

metadata.name: Stairs #51
metadata.description:
Algorithmically generated stairs. Inspired by Dutch graphic artist M.C. Escher.

Arrangement, style and color set are unique in each edition.

However:
Any edition can generate an infinite amount of arrangements & styles and allows you to cycle through the color sets, so that you can find your perfect piece. 
The preview is based on the initial, randomized arrangement & style.


Created in Vanilla JS on Canvas2D

Controls:
R - Generate Stairs
B - Change Background
C - Change Color
D - Change Style
A - Restart Animation
S - Download Image


DUTCH AUCTION:
The price will start out at 5ꜩ and will decrease by 1ꜩ every 10 minutes. It will remain at 1ꜩ.
